description:
A discussion about contributing to CLJS - the good, bad and ugly

A coding session using REPtiLe. Reptiles like bugs and there were a few on display.

If you want to run REPtiLe yourself or contribute, the repos are at
https://github.com/raymcdermott/reptile-tail (server)
https://github.com/raymcdermott/reptile-tongue (browser UI)

title: Apropos 30 Sep
description:
- News: a quick chat about Reveal. Check it out at https://vlaaad.github.io/reveal/
- REPL session: A game tree for tic-tac-toe. Eric did a great job despite the heckling :)
- This was our first experiment with Discord, it was good and we will get better and smoother with it as we learn!
- Finally, thanks for tipping us over the 1k subscribers this month!!

To join the Discord server, here is an invite that is good for the first 25 to get on board:

title: Apropos 14 October 2020
description:
Demo of Portal by the author Chris Badahdah (https://github.com/djblue) with appropriate grillings and homework from the panel :)

It's a really great way to explore data that was previously inaccessible. It's in the same space as Reveal and the closed source REBL from the company formerly known as Cognitect.

It was streamed live on the Apropos discord server which is open to all.

Here is an invite to make it super easy!
https://discord.gg/hgxAyQaeuX
